19:33.580 --> 19:36.705
No one will ever see your actual circumstances again.

19:38.127 --> 19:42.034
The live filter, because fantasy is the new reality.

19:46.978 --> 19:53.208
Hey Heritage, I'm so excited to step into this new series of conversations we're calling unfiltered family.

19:53.228 --> 20:05.106
It's an invitation for all of us, whether we're a family of one seeking to dig into greater community or a great big nuclear family or anything in between because the reality is

20:05.218 --> 20:10.704
Our family, however that looks for us and however we define it, is probably a crazy, beautiful mess.

20:11.144 --> 20:18.551
And one, where we're tempted, at least from time to time, to live out of a filtered version of what family is for us.

20:18.952 --> 20:28.221
Where we dig into the spaces that are happy and connected, and we want other people to see only those spaces that are happy and connected.

20:28.942 --> 20:33.106
But we've been asking the question, what would it look like if we dared to live life unfiltered?

20:33.538 --> 20:48.772
When we think that it's there in those unfiltered spaces, the spaces of courage and intention, where we will find the healing, the purpose, and the adventure that God has for each of us, in each of our families, however we define them.

20:48.792 --> 20:50.234
So let's dig in together.

20:50.574 --> 20:58.521
Today we're gonna be looking at a number of different scriptures, primarily in the book of Deuteronomy, chapter six, and in first Corinthians.

20:58.802 --> 21:03.346
So I encourage you to get a Bible and turn there, get ready to press in with us.

21:03.490 --> 21:15.244
But you know, all of this conversation around family has me remembering a group of people that I spent so much time with, that I traveled with, that became like family for me, even though we weren't related.

21:15.865 --> 21:21.732
When I was in college, I traveled with five other college students representing our school for the better part of a year.

21:22.233 --> 21:29.842
We traveled thousands of miles across the United States and Canada, all squeezed into a little van.

21:30.082 --> 21:41.941
If you don't think that traveling thousands of miles in a van with six people doesn't cause you to appreciate and be annoyed by a group of people, a lot like your own family, then I don't know what will.

21:42.622 --> 21:55.161
Now, there was one week in particular, because you see, we had been traveling from venue to venue, from camp to camp, from church to church, representing our school and helping lead people in worship.

21:55.642 --> 21:58.226
And on this one particular week, we had been on the road

21:58.338 --> 21:59.099
four weeks.

21:59.199 --> 22:04.547
We had just spent several weeks at different camps in the middle of the summer and we were exhausted.

22:05.208 --> 22:18.126
Part of what travel then looked like for us was because we didn't have GPS yet or even smartphones, the places we were going to would provide us with preferred directions, a way to get where they were located.

22:18.446 --> 22:23.133
And a lot of these spaces, especially the camps, were located in the middle of nowhere.

22:23.594 --> 22:23.954
So,

22:24.354 --> 22:29.280
We're headed to this one destination after we've been serving for several weeks together.

22:29.841 --> 22:33.546
And the directions that we receive are a little bit different than perhaps what we're used to.

22:33.966 --> 22:43.238
Instead of listing the numbers of streets and addresses, it's given to us in a context that's very much rural.

22:44.119 --> 22:49.426
We were given directions that said, traveled down Old Houghton Road.

22:49.890 --> 22:52.013
And then you'll get to a church.

22:52.313 --> 22:55.498
Now, the challenge is nobody called the road old Houghton Road anymore.

22:55.538 --> 22:56.178
It had a number.

22:56.599 --> 23:01.265
So we traveled down what we were pretty sure was old Houghton Road until we got to a church.

23:01.626 --> 23:05.070
And then the direction said, after you get to the little church, turn right.

23:05.691 --> 23:06.372
So we turned right.

23:07.053 --> 23:13.121
And then it said, travel down that road for a couple of miles, and you'll see what used to be Frank's hardware on the left.

23:13.882 --> 23:17.407
So we traveled down the road for a couple of miles, and there was an old dilapidated building.

23:18.028 --> 23:19.570
Look like it could have been Frank's hardware.

23:19.874 --> 23:27.986
So we felt like we were on the right path and then followed the rest of the directions until it told us that we should be arriving at the entrance to the camp.

23:28.988 --> 23:33.655
When we got there, we were dismayed to discover we were in the middle of a farmer's field.

23:34.396 --> 23:36.439
We were not at all where we were supposed to be.

23:37.160 --> 23:44.751
So we backtracked a little bit, went back into town and asked the locals if they had heard of and knew where to get to this camp.

23:44.771 --> 23:46.514
None of them had even heard tell of the place.

23:47.010 --> 23:53.338
So then we found another invention of the old days of payphone and called our contact at the space we were supposed to be.

23:53.378 --> 24:01.208
They were shocked to find out we were three hours in the wrong direction from where we were supposed to be.

24:01.228 --> 24:05.673
You see, they had given us directions that assumed a different starting point.

24:05.693 --> 24:12.562
That story, that experience of mine revealed something to me that's true on road trips and it's true for families too.

24:12.738 --> 24:16.927
You see, in order to get where we want to go, we have to know where we're coming from.

24:17.689 --> 24:24.644
That's kind of the foundational truth that we're going to be digging into as we look at living a life unfiltered in our families today.

24:25.045 --> 24:29.635
This idea that in order to get where we want to go, we need to know where we're coming from.

24:30.417 --> 24:30.898
You see,

24:31.106 --> 24:39.597
I think we all have experiences in different parts of life, especially when it comes to family, where it feels like we've been following the directions given to us.

24:39.998 --> 24:44.404
The directions that say we should achieve success and no matter what it costs.

24:44.424 --> 24:52.174
We should keep our kids busy and involved in all the things so that they become well-rounded individuals and productive members of society.

24:52.455 --> 24:56.160
We should seek to earn more, have more, give more, develop more.

24:56.480 --> 25:00.946
We should be all about pursuit of a shared dream.

25:01.122 --> 25:01.583
and goal.

25:02.524 --> 25:13.939
And inevitably, at some point along the way, even when we've been following the directions that we've been given, we lift up our head and discover where we are is not where we thought we would be.

25:13.960 --> 25:18.125
And we kind of wonder how on earth did we get here?

25:19.407 --> 25:21.790
We're not the only ones who have dealt with that question.

25:21.850 --> 25:30.482
In fact, there's a story of a people of God called Israel who have been promised a land that God wants to give them.

25:31.106 --> 25:41.999
But along the way, they've taken detours, they've made some mistakes, they've ended up in a space when we intersect with their story that is not where they thought they would be by now.

25:42.019 --> 25:58.098
And what we discover in their story as a broader family and what we can discover for ours when it comes to understanding how to experience and live into the goodness God has for us, how to find the healing and adventure and purpose that we feel like we're invited into.

25:58.434 --> 26:05.024
how to actually receive what it is that we've been pursuing all along and ended up, we don't know where.

26:06.306 --> 26:17.202
Part of what their story reminds us of is this foundational truth that we're talking about, that in order to get where we want to go, we have to know where we've come from.

26:18.050 --> 26:29.205
And in it, we start to see some invitations for you and your family, me and mine, and even our broader heritage family about what it looks like to be people of courage living life unfiltered.

26:29.666 --> 26:36.175
So let's dig in to see how their story plays out and what it means for us in Deuteronomy chapter six.

26:36.756 --> 26:41.482
Again, we're picking up their story after years of a long road trip.

26:41.502 --> 26:47.250
They are in a space where where they are is not where they wanted to be by now.

26:47.426 --> 26:49.528
They also know a new day is coming.

26:49.929 --> 26:55.795
A new opportunity is ahead of them to step into new things and finally receive what it is that they've been waiting for.

26:56.336 --> 26:59.659
So we pick it up in Deuteronomy chapter six, verse three.

27:00.340 --> 27:13.034
Their leader says this to them, here Israel, and be careful to obey so that it may go well with you and that you may increase greatly in a land flowing with milk and honey, just as the Lord, the God of your ancestors promised you.

27:13.694 --> 27:17.138
Here, oh Israel, the Lord our God, the Lord,

27:17.314 --> 27:17.855
is one.

27:18.936 --> 27:24.985
Believe it or not, right here in these few lines, we see a little bit of what it looks like to live life unfiltered.

27:25.586 --> 27:32.035
We see that living life unfiltered takes courage to be honest about where we are and how we got here.

27:32.555 --> 27:36.541
Living life unfiltered takes courage to be honest about where we are and how we got here.

27:36.942 --> 27:42.930
You see, the writer begins this part of the conversation with a sense of

27:43.138 --> 27:48.765
where we are is not the place that we have been waiting to get into, but it's coming.

27:49.446 --> 28:08.889
And leading up to this point, Moses actually reminds the people who are listening to him of moment after moment after moment of God's faithfulness and their failure of spaces that have brought them to this place that caused a 40 day journey to become a 40 year trek in the wilderness.

28:09.970 --> 28:12.914
It is an immediate invitation to be honest.

28:13.218 --> 28:15.381
about where they are and how they got here.

28:16.022 --> 28:30.041
Even the declaration here, Israel, the Lord our God, the Lord is one God, was a tacit reminder of their failure to pursue the one true God and tendency to give themselves to false gods and idols.

28:30.862 --> 28:42.738
It's a loaded moment that is full of courage and honesty about how they got where they are and what it is that God wants to do in and through them even

28:43.106 --> 28:54.017
Now, by pointing out that they weren't where they wanted to be yet, there's an invitation or an expectation that they can yet step into that place of promise.

28:54.637 --> 29:02.124
By reminding them of the patterns that had gotten them to that space, there's an invitation to choose a new way, to find a new pattern.

29:02.785 --> 29:06.268
And the same invitation is there for me and for you on the journey that we're on.

29:06.669 --> 29:09.752
However we define family, whatever it looks like for us.

29:10.433 --> 29:11.954
You see, for Israel,

29:12.418 --> 29:23.009
When they looked back at what got them to this point, when they looked back at where they were and how they got there, they would discover moments of great courage and cowardice.

29:23.630 --> 29:28.736
They would see moments of incredible faithfulness and deep sinfulness.

29:29.877 --> 29:41.970
They would, if they looked back in their history, see spaces and places of repeated brokenness, cycles that had taken root over generation after generation,

29:42.050 --> 29:42.991
after generation.

29:44.133 --> 29:54.545
And there's a very real sense when these words that we just read are declared over them to find a new way, to choose a new path, to seek something different.

29:55.366 --> 29:58.110
But to do that, they have to be honest.

29:58.130 --> 30:01.654
They have to have courage to look at where they are and how they got there.

30:02.776 --> 30:05.038
They're not the only ones who have to do that.

30:05.098 --> 30:11.186
In fact, just like the nation of Israel that we see in the scriptures here, our families are a mixed bag too.

30:11.394 --> 30:15.619
a mixed bag of blessing and what we might even say curses.

30:15.959 --> 30:29.274
A mixed bag of courage and cowardice, of great decisions and poor ones, of histories that have moved us closer to the things of God and moved us much further away than what he would want for us.

30:30.496 --> 30:32.998
This is the truth for any of us.

30:33.339 --> 30:39.666
It's not a space of shame, but a space where we're again encouraged to have courage, to assess, to look,

30:39.906 --> 30:42.890
to be honest with where we are and how we got here.

30:44.593 --> 30:58.634
There are in each family, patterns of brokenness that seem to kind of move from branch of family tree to branch of family tree, from family unit to family unit to family unit.

30:59.315 --> 31:03.881
Spaces and places where there are things in our histories we'd rather not look at.

31:04.322 --> 31:05.544
We'd rather not discuss.

31:05.904 --> 31:07.287
Certainly things we don't celebrate.

31:08.228 --> 31:09.650
Spaces of brokenness,

31:09.954 --> 31:17.726
infidelity of addiction, of choice after choice after choice that have moved us away from God's goodness.

31:18.587 --> 31:35.252
We all can see these things if we are courageous enough to peel back the layers in our family journey, whether we are talking about the family we're born into or adopted into or the broader history of that family.

31:37.556 --> 31:39.218
But we're not invited

31:39.426 --> 31:49.618
to stay there were actually just invited as Moses revealed to his people to have courage to be honest about where we are, how we got there.

31:51.022 --> 31:53.490
So I'm going to invite you for a moment to dig in.

31:53.858 --> 32:02.090
to at some point in the coming week dig in, take a notebook and begin to think back of the history and trajectory of your family.

32:02.351 --> 32:09.081
To think back through the patterns of your life, of your family, where you can see goodness at play.

32:09.361 --> 32:18.735
The things that make you say, I'm so glad I get to be part of a family that is courageous, that chooses the more difficult way, that offers life and love.

32:19.496 --> 32:23.602
But also to write down, to track the things, the patterns,

32:24.610 --> 32:27.335
you would give anything to make different.

32:28.478 --> 32:42.546
Those spaces of faithlessness, of pain, of addiction, of brokenness, those things where maybe you've become convinced that because they've always been broken, they always will be.

32:42.658 --> 32:49.066
Because divorce is a generational cycle in your family, it must mean that that's coming for you as well.

32:49.447 --> 32:57.157
That because infidelity is something that has happened generation after generation after generation, though you don't like it, it must be a foregone conclusion.

32:57.437 --> 33:02.944
What are those things where you have seen brokenness and pain in your family?

33:03.405 --> 33:07.510
He would give anything to see it become something different.

33:07.530 --> 33:10.674
You see, living life unfiltered takes courage.

33:11.010 --> 33:14.294
It takes courage to be honest about where we are and how we got here.

33:15.195 --> 33:20.580
But when we do that, we begin to live into something altogether different.

33:21.642 --> 33:32.393
I don't know where you set in the spectrum of this, but some of us can find things in our families that are so deep, so painful, so entrenched.

33:32.674 --> 33:34.976
