37:00.701 --> 37:06.828
Confess your sins to each other and pray for each other that you may be healed.

37:06.848 --> 37:20.082
There's a very real indication throughout the Scriptures that when it comes to the broken patterns and histories of our lives, the decisions, maybe we aren't even the ones who made those decisions but they've impacted how we live our life today.

37:20.386 --> 37:36.924
that by bringing them into the light, by finding others who are on this journey with Jesus and being honest about where we are and how we got here, by confessing them, that that is the space where healing starts to come into play.

37:38.446 --> 37:45.954
Now you can see why I said living life unfiltered takes courage to be honest about where we are and how we got here.

37:48.457 --> 37:49.298
That leads us

37:49.570 --> 37:52.654
to the next invitation for us or the next space of courage.

37:53.555 --> 37:57.480
Living life unfiltered takes courage to be honest about where we are and how we got here.

37:57.821 --> 38:00.565
It also takes courage to choose a new path.

38:01.606 --> 38:07.914
You see, on that road trip long ago, there was no way for us to just keep going down the road we had been going down.

38:08.175 --> 38:09.356
It was gonna take us nowhere.

38:10.117 --> 38:16.786
We also couldn't backtrack the way that we came because that wasn't gonna take us to the destination we need to get to either.

38:17.090 --> 38:30.323
And if we're honest, I think in our families especially, but in a lot of places in life, those are the two options we feel like we're faced with, to keep on keeping on or backtrack and try to fix what's gone wrong in the past.

38:31.745 --> 38:44.658
But I believe the unfiltered life that Jesus invites us into by his death and resurrection, the unfiltered life that Moses is actually even speaking to the people of Israel about is an invitation down a new path.

38:44.770 --> 38:49.441
one that we may not even have seen before, and one I don't know that we can see outside of Jesus.

38:50.202 --> 38:56.697
It's seen as Moses continues his invitation to these people in Israel.

38:57.519 --> 39:03.954
He says, love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, and with all your strength.

39:04.578 --> 39:07.622
These commandments that I give you today are to be on your hearts.

39:08.122 --> 39:09.424
Impress them on your children.

39:09.724 --> 39:14.731
Talk about them when you sit at home and when you walk along the road, when you lie down and when you get up.

39:15.031 --> 39:18.135
Tie them as symbols on your hands and bind them on your foreheads.

39:18.455 --> 39:21.800
Write them on the door frames of your houses and on your gates.

39:23.822 --> 39:27.847
You see, the invitation is to a new path, the path of love.

39:28.128 --> 39:33.234
He begins that part of the scripture saying, love the Lord your God with all of who you are.

39:34.146 --> 39:37.464
And then there's something fascinating that happens here.

39:37.886 --> 39:41.746
It's as if this new path will require new patterns of us.

39:42.306 --> 39:49.681
because the writer goes out of his way to say, this new path of love is going to require such a different way of living.

39:49.901 --> 39:53.107
You're going to have to keep that in front of you all the time.

39:53.508 --> 39:55.051
Never stop talking about it.

39:55.352 --> 39:58.217
Make sure your kids get it and get it and get it.

39:58.518 --> 40:01.103
Write it so it's the first thing you see when you enter your house.

40:01.384 --> 40:03.909
Write it so it's the first thing you see when you look at your hands.

40:04.209 --> 40:04.690
Write it

40:04.802 --> 40:17.586
around the house so much, speak about it so much, interact with it so much, this new way of thinking and living, this way of love, that it's like it is written deep in your heart.

40:18.242 --> 40:25.493
You see, we're invited to have courage to walk down a new path, the path of love, but it will require new patterns of us.

40:25.933 --> 40:31.762
This is why the work before of looking at where are we and how did we get here is so important.

40:32.183 --> 40:40.775
Not so that we sit in a space of shame or so that we wonder how we even got here, but so that we can choose a new path with new patterns.

40:41.617 --> 40:45.202
It's not just enough to bring these things to light.

40:45.666 --> 40:49.470
but to step forward in a new way, the way of love.

40:50.251 --> 40:57.079
And I know for some of us in our family lives, we have not experienced the depth of healthy love.

40:57.699 --> 41:08.591
We've seen it when it's conditional on how we perform, or we've been in abusive spaces, or we've interacted mostly with people who are passive aggressive.

41:08.611 --> 41:13.216
We may not yet have experienced the fullness or goodness of love.

41:13.857 --> 41:14.738
And so we wonder,

41:15.330 --> 41:17.292
How do we choose the path of love?

41:19.114 --> 41:27.784
What I'm hopeful in is the reality that the invitation of this kind of love is not something that we manufacture on our own.

41:28.645 --> 41:39.036
In fact, the more I journey with Jesus, the more I'm convinced that the kind of love he invites us into is actually a spiritual gift.

41:39.636 --> 41:44.722
It's a gift that he wants to give us so it can come to life in us and allow us to walk it out.

41:45.122 --> 41:55.154
Let me show you in the book of 1 Corinthians, chapter 12 and 13, where the writer has actually just written a series of

41:55.330 --> 41:58.695
bullet points about different spiritual gifts.

41:58.715 --> 42:01.520
And if you've been in the church for a while, you're probably familiar with them.

42:01.800 --> 42:06.228
He talks about gifts like prophecy and healing and knowledge and wisdom.

42:06.468 --> 42:15.583
He speaks about these gifts that are built for building one another up, the ability to speak in different languages and to connect people with God as never before.

42:16.224 --> 42:22.674
But then he reveals that each of those gifts, as awesome as they are, are temporary.

42:23.714 --> 42:34.227
They only serve us here and now, but there's one gift, one spiritual gift that is eternal, one spiritual gift that we will live out in heaven.

42:34.848 --> 42:35.849
And it's the gift of love.

42:35.929 --> 42:36.390
Watch this.

42:36.990 --> 42:45.941
He says, so eagerly desire the greater gifts and I will show you the most excellent way.

42:47.083 --> 42:51.228
And then he starts to talk about love and defines it this way for us.

42:52.189 --> 42:53.010
Love is patient.

42:53.538 --> 42:54.319
Love is kind.

42:55.000 --> 42:55.821
It does not envy.

42:55.841 --> 42:57.323
It does not boast.

42:57.703 --> 42:58.584
It is not proud.

42:59.085 --> 43:00.607
It does not dishonor others.

43:00.707 --> 43:02.109
It is not self-seeking.

43:02.409 --> 43:03.931
It is not easily angered.

43:03.971 --> 43:05.373
It keeps no record of wrongs.

43:05.773 --> 43:09.318
Love does not delight in evil but rejoices with the truth.

43:09.638 --> 43:15.666
It always protects, always trusts, always hope, always perseveres.

43:16.962 --> 43:24.653
This is the kind of love that leads us down a new path, the path of life and resurrection with Jesus.

43:25.014 --> 43:41.719
This is the kind of love that invites us into new patterns, patterns that reveal spaces of patience and kindness, of spaces that aren't full of envy or boastfulness, but are honoring one another, are seeking the best, are persevering together.

43:41.859 --> 43:46.706
Imagine what your family, whatever it looks like would be like.

43:47.298 --> 43:50.842
if just one of you chose the way of love.

43:52.844 --> 44:00.253
And that's our invitation today because a new way of living, a new path and a new pattern, it begins with you.

44:00.293 --> 44:04.517
This day, you can choose a different way.

44:05.198 --> 44:13.587
Those mistakes of the past, those broken patterns of what have been, they do not need to define you or your family any longer.

44:14.288 --> 44:15.890
You see, within the scriptures,

44:16.066 --> 44:25.299
In that book of Deuteronomy, even later the writer reminds those who are listening that they are the people who saw God turn curses into blessings.

44:26.161 --> 44:31.829
And this is what he can do in and through each of us.

44:31.849 --> 44:34.493
For us, in the spaces that we occupy.

44:36.095 --> 44:43.666
If love is a gift, it's one he's inviting us to receive, to choose, to step into and to pursue his never before.

44:44.482 --> 44:49.710
That's our heart's cry, our desire for you to live life unfiltered with courage.

44:49.970 --> 44:54.717
To be honest about where you are and how you got here, but then to choose a new path and new pattern.

44:55.819 --> 45:00.826
